 of concern about environmental issues, human rights, and international peace. God in the Tumult of the Global Square explores all of these directions, based on a five-year Luce Foundation project that involved religious leaders, scholars, and public figures in workshops held in Cairo, Moscow, Delhi, Shanghai, Buenos Aires, and Santa Barbara. In this book, the voices of these religious observers around the world express both the hopes and fears about new forms of religion in the global age.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aGlobalizationxReligious aspects. 0aReligion and civil society. 0aReligion and politics. 0aReligion and sociology. 7aRELIGION / Religion, Politics & State.2bisacsh  aaccountability.  abrotherhood.  acomparative politics.  aconflict.  acultural imperialism.  aenvironmental concerns.  aglobal citizenship.  aglobal era.  aglobal religion.  aglobalization.  ahardship.  ahuman rights.  ainternational peace.  aluce foundation.  amorality.  apolitical.  apower of god.  apower struggle.  areligion in the 21st century.  areligion.  areligious activists.  areligious differences.  areligious leaders.  areligious protest.  areligious scholars.  areligious studies.  asecurity.  aspiritual.  atransnational civil society.  aviolence.  aworldwide community.1 aGriego, Dinah, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSoboslai, John, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028347340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095932340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520959323423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520959323/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  Univ